<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Thermostat And Coolant Filter -
        Thermostat
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Thermostat</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or possibly death, always allow engine to cool first. Wrap a thick,
                        heavy cloth around radiator cap. Push down and loosen the cap slowly to its first notch
                        position. Then pause a moment. This will avoid possible scalding by hot water or steam. Continue
                        to turn the cap to the left and remove it.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200804" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3331.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Thermostat Outlet Tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant Outlet Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat Gasket (Square Cross Section)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the three bolts that secure the outlet tube to the water pump housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Some engines were equipped with a thermostat having a separate gasket. Remove and discard
                        thermostat and thermostat gasket. Replace with new thermostat with integral seal. Refer to
                        "Installation".
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thermostat with integral seal from the water pump housing.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
